casebody.data:
Jennifer JAMES, Plaintiff/Appellant,
v.
FARMERS INSURANCE CO., INC., Defendant/Respondent. ED 106505 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, DIVISION THREE. Filed: November 13, 2018
Motion for Rehearing and/or Transfer to Supreme Court Denied December 17, 2018
Application for Transfer Denied March 5, 2019 David C. Knieriem, 7711 Bonhomme, Suite 850, Clayton, MO 63105, Joseph P. Rice III, Austin D. Crowe, Co-Counsel, 160 S. Broadview, 4 th Floor, Cape Girardeau, MO 63703, For Plaintiff/Appellant. Luke R. Hertenstein, Scott D. Hofer, 1200 Main Street, Suite 2200, Kansas City, MO 64105, For Defendant/Respondent. Before Sherri B. Sullivan, P.J., Lawrence E. Mooney, J., and James M. Dowd, J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM.

Jennifer James (Appellant) appeals the trial court's judgment granting summary judgment in favor of Farmers Insurance Co., Inc. (Farmers). Appellant's sole point on appeal claims the trial court erred in granting summary judgment in favor of Farmers because Appellant was entitled to underinsured motorist coverage under Farmers' motor vehicle liability insurance policy. We affirm.

An extended opinion would have no precedential value. The parties have been furnished with a memorandum for their information only, setting forth the reasons for this order pursuant to Rule 84.16(b).
